<title>USA: Datametrics names CFO, COO.</title>
<headline>Datametrics names CFO, COO.</headline>
<dateline>WOODLAND HILLS 1997-04-17</dateline>
<text>
<p>Datametrics Corp on Thursday said it promoted James Sturgeon to the post of chief operating officer and Kenneth Polak to the post of chief financial officer.</p>
<p>Both executives replace Adrien Maught in the respective positions. Maught, who had been president, chief operating officer and acting chief financial officer, retains his position as president of the company, a spokeswoman said.</p>
<p>Sturgeon had been the company's vice president of manufacturing/operations, and Polak had been its controller.</p>
